body:
Continuing after issue 36092, I ended up with the following code:

``` rust
use std::iter::{Iterator,Peekable};

trait PeekableTrait {
    type Item;
    fn peek(&mut self) -> Option<&<Self as Iterator>::Item> where Self: Iterator;
}

impl<I: Iterator> PeekableTrait for Peekable<I> {
    type Item = I::Item;
    fn peek(&mut self) -> Option<&<Self as Iterator>::Item> where Self: Iterator {
        Peekable::peek(&mut self)
    }
}
```

Compiling it fails with:

```
error: main function not found

error[E0308]: mismatched types
  --> <anon>:11:9
   |
11 |         Peekable::peek(&mut self)
   |         ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ expected struct `std::iter::Peekable`, found type parameter
   |
   = note: expected type `std::option::Option<&<std::iter::Peekable<I> as std::iter::Iterator>::Item>`
   = note:    found type `std::option::Option<&<I as std::iter::Iterator>::Item>`

error: aborting due to previous error
```

FWIW, because this was created incrementally, it turns out the type Item is not necessary, and removing it doesn't change anything.

Anyways, talchas on irc figured how to make it compile:

``` rust
use std::iter::{Iterator,Peekable};

trait PeekableTrait: Iterator {
    fn peek(&mut self) -> Option<&<Self as Iterator>::Item>;
}

impl<I: Iterator> PeekableTrait for Peekable<I> {
    fn peek(&mut self) -> Option<&<Self as Iterator>::Item> {
        Peekable::peek(&mut self)
    }
}
```

But simply adding redundant `where Self: ITerator` clauses causes the same E0308 error:

``` rust
use std::iter::{Iterator,Peekable};

trait PeekableTrait: Iterator {
    fn peek(&mut self) -> Option<&<Self as Iterator>::Item> where Self: Iterator;
}

impl<I: Iterator> PeekableTrait for Peekable<I> {
    fn peek(&mut self) -> Option<&<Self as Iterator>::Item> where Self: Iterator {
        Peekable::peek(&mut self)
    }
}
```

Relatedly, the message `expected struct `std::iter::Peekable`, found type parameter` doesn't make sense to me and I can't reconcile it with the notes that follow it (expected type... found type...)
